Description: Good Seed is a superfood company that has re-invented the veggie burger by using only real, minimally processed foods.
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: Good Seed is a superfood company that has re-invented the veggie burger by using only real, minimally processed foods and providing a ""foodie"" approved great tasting product that was previously lacking in this category.   Good Seed sells to retailers, restaurants and bars and we are the #1 seller at the retailers we are in.  Most options in this category are made primarily of highly processed soy, wheat, and corn but Good Seed fills the void by using  only REAL minimally processed foods.    We are in some of the hottest categories in food.  The organic food market (18% CAGR), plant-based food and beverage (8% CAGR), frozen meat alternatives (8% CAGR)the 40% of Americans who are ""flexitarians"" who are striving to eat more plant-based meals.  Innovators in their category in nutrient dense and plant-based foods are experiencing 2-3x revenue multiples on their valuation as compared to less than 1% for regular grocery.  Big names in Silicon Valley are also jumping in to invest in the meat alternatives category.  Bill Gates, Co-Founders of Twitter, Pay-Pal, Google and funds that funded Facebook, Pay-Pal, Napster, and Sun Microsystems are all investing in meat alternatives.  Bill Gates says that ""Meeting the demand for meat is a big market opportunity.  Innovation in this sector has tremendous market potential.""   Good Seed is selling at retailers and restaurants around Austin and surrounding areas.  We are currently starting with Whole Foods and Natural grocers and will focus on the rest of Texas this year.  Once we are in 15-20 Whole Foods locations we will establish distribution with the main natural foods distributor and have access to over 3,000 retailers in the country.   We have scaled up  our production to a co-packing facility that can produce up to 20,000 lbs of product per day.  We are raising funds to add packaging equipment, printed packaging, bulk ingredients, and a sales and marketing team to help with a national roll-out.
Industry Groups: Food and Beverage, Travel and Tourism

Description: Cloud-based IT Systems Management
Headquarters Regions: Greater Houston Area, Southern US
Full Description: ITSCAPE provides a new generation of low-cost, high-quality, easy-to-use cloud-based system management products. Companies are losing $26.5B every year due to outages and unplanned downtime. A major contributor to these outages is the difficulty managing the rapidly increasing complexity of IT environments created by virtualization and cloud technologies. Business applications and processes are more complex to manage as they are no longer contained to a few servers in a datacenter, but spread out across many physical and virtual servers inside and outside a company. This creates a lack of visibility of where applications reside and what servers or components they are dependent on. IT managers often have no idea of which servers, databases, connection, and more support their companies business-critical services. Simple changes to a single server can cause major outages.  ITSCAPE provides a new, cloud-based, affordable, and easy way to perform application discovery, application dependency mapping map, and change tracking in an IT environment –including elements that are physical, virtual, or in the cloud.  With ITSCAPE, IT managers get an accurate and comprehensive understanding of all of the servers, applications, databases, and communications in their datacenter, see the relationships between these IT components, and get clear visibility into the IT systems that support their company’s business critical services.  This information can then be used to pinpoint or prevent issues that cause performance problems, outages and downtime.  ITSCAPE helps IT managers more quickly resolve service issues, keep an accurate view of "who changed what when." ITSCAPE can also be used to prepare to optimize IT systems or for datacenter transformation initiatives such as  virtualization, consolidation, and/or migration.  Traditional auto-discovery and dependency mapping solutions are expensive to purchase, install, and maintain. ITSCAPE is changing this.  ITSCAPE requires no hardware, expensive training classes, or consulting services and is priced to be affordable for small to medium sized businesses.  Next, ITSCAPE can be set up and functioning in minutes, is self-maintaining, requires no upgrades, and has little to no impact on existing IT systems. Finally, it can provide initial discovery and dependency mapping results in an hour or less and is easy-to-use and understand by both technical and non-technical staff.

Description: Helping streamers create gaming tournaments for their fans and viewers
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Streamers are offline for 12+ hours a day and any additional time offline like taking a couple days off or going on vacation can directly impact their revenue potential. In short, anytime away from streaming is money lost. It causes a drop in viewership and engagement which leads to a decrease in subscriptions, donations and bit cheers from twitch followers. It can also lead to a drop in advertising revenue from twitch, weaker results for their sponsors, and decreased merchandise and affiliate sales. Our team has developed a platform that enables streamers to host their own gaming tournaments for their fans and viewers to play in. We're making it easy for streamers to find sponsors for their events by automatically providing them with a list of companies willing to sponsor the event and give away prizes like merchandise, digital experiences (for example, playing with the streamer during their stream), free trials, and much more. Our mission is to make esports competitions available to all gamers and we're working with streamers to make that happen. Now, anyone can compete in tournaments with games like Fortnite, League of Legends, PUBG, and CS:GO.
Industry Groups: Advertising, Apps, Content and Publishing, Gaming, Media and Entertainment, Sales and Marketing, Software, Sports, Video

Description: Cyneta Networks, Inc. develops hardware and software for wireless data networks. The company offers Intelligent Packet Control Node, which
Headquarters Regions: Dallas/Fort Worth Metroplex, Southern US
Full Description: Cyneta Networks will be recognized as the global leader in providing intelligent data networking solutions for next generation wireless networks. Cyneta Networks was established to develop and deploy the Intelligent Packet Control Node™, an innovative new network element that optimizes IP communications, significantly reducing costs and generating new revenues for wireless carriers.  Founded with a vision to provide a new form of visibility and control to wireless packet data networks, Cyneta Networks has developed the first "intelligent" monitoring system that provides wireless carriers with deep visibility into the performance of their data services for particular users and user classes. To provide intelligent monitoring, Cyneta Networks has taken an innovative architectural approach to wireless data monitoring.  Cyneta’s solution is designed around a centrally located packet-processing platform that provides a comprehensive view of the operator’s services, looking at every packet traversing the mobile core network.  Cyneta has incorporated this technology into an advanced network and service monitoring solution that extracts key information about the performance of the network and the applications and services that run on it. This unique approach offers several advantages for end-to-end fault, performance, and service management.  It provides operators with the most complete set of network, subscriber, and services information, allowing for the visibility of not just service quality but how that quality relates to the subscriber or classes of subscribers.  The result is increased operational efficiencies, improved user experience, enhanced revenue opportunities, and a greater acceptance of wireless data in the business and consumer markets. Headquartered in Richardson, Texas with additional sales and development offices in the Netherlands and India, Cyneta Networks is partnered with leading Operational Support System (OSS), Original Equipment Manufacturer (OEM), and System Integrator (SI) companies to provide intelligent monitoring solutions to wireless network operators around the world.
Industry Groups: Artificial Intelligence (AI), Data and Analytics, Hardware, Internet Services, Science and Engineering
Top 5 Investors: Partech, Battery Ventures, Crescendo Ventures, Vortex Partners, Taleria Ventures

Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: OwnClouders is an open-source community that offers self-hosted web applications with sync clients and sharing. It also enables uses to access their files through a web interface while offering a platform to easily view and sync their contacts, calendars, and bookmarks across all devices and edit them as well.  Being extendable via an API for applications and plugins, OwnClouders has minimal server requirements and requires no special permissions. The business model of OwnCloud Inc. is very similar to other open-source companies, offering services and support around OwnCloud for the enterprise. The company is dedicated to working in the open, accelerating development in the areas of its customers' needs while enabling a completely open development process where everybody can contribute. The company makes it possible for developers to work full time on OwnCloud, organizing OwnCloud events, marketing OwnCloud to a wider audience and supporting companies, governments, and schools in their deployments. OwnCloud started with a keynote by Frank Karlitschek at Camp KDE’10 where he talked about the need of a self-controlled free and open-source cloud. Two years later, Karlitschek announced the start of OwnCloud Inc.

And in exchange, establishments are receiving relevant metrics like views, conversions, churn-rate and visit duration from customers coming through the door (that use Boldr).
